Author:
Vol / Page: 13
Edition:
Quote: In the time that we spent on the farm with Peter Fisher we reached the conclusion that he is applying in his approach to his job that mixture of qualities which can best be summed up in two words, 'good cowmanship.' And as we have said on many occasions before - good cowmanship - the natural capacity to get the best from each individual member of the herd - is the highest common factor in successful dairy farming.
